---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Support | Lone Meeple"
  description="Support and contact for the Lone Meeple app — the solo board-gaming companion."
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-bark">
          Lone Meeple Support
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-bark/50">The solo board-gaming companion</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-article">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, problems, or ideas? Email
          <a href="mailto:fjordlabs.app@gmail.com">fjordlabs.app@gmail.com</a>
          and we will get back to you as soon as we can. Feature requests from
          solo gamers are always welcome.
        </p>

        <h2>Common questions</h2>

        <h3>How do I restore my Pro purchase?</h3>
        <p>
          Open the app, go to <strong>Settings</strong> and tap
          <strong>Restore purchase</strong>. Pro is a one-time purchase tied to
          your account and your Apple ID, so it can be restored on any device.
        </p>

        <h3>I switched phones — where is my journal?</h3>
        <p>
          Sign in with the same Apple or Google account you used before and
          your games, plays and campaigns will sync back automatically.
        </p>

        <h3>How do I export my data?</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Settings → Export backup</strong> creates a complete JSON
          file of your journal that you can save anywhere. You can import it
          back at any time.
        </p>

        <h3>How do I delete my account?</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Settings → Delete account &amp; my data</strong> permanently
          removes your account and everything you have logged. This cannot be
          undone, so consider exporting a backup first.
        </p>

        <h3>A game is missing from the search catalog</h3>
        <p>
          You can always add any game manually by typing its name. The search
          catalog grows over time; if a title you expected is missing, tell us
          by email and we will look into it.
        </p>

        <h2>Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Lone Meeple stores only your own data. Read the full
          <a href="/lone-meeple/privacy">privacy policy</a>.
        </p>

        <p>
          Lone Meeple is an unofficial companion app. It is not affiliated
          with any game or publisher; all game names and trademarks belong to
          their respective owners. Game catalog data and images are provided
          by BoardGameGeek.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
